name: gatk-collect-oxog-metrics.4.1.8.0-3.0
body:
- add param to include analysis of unpaired reads
- add param `-paired` as input of the process
- use string instead of bool for param `-paired` in nf file

name: gatk-collect-oxog-metrics.4.1.8.0-2.0
body:
- set `-MIN_INS=0` and `-MAX_INS=0` instead of defaults to allow unpaired reads
- add test case for scenario of single ended reads
- bump version to `4.1.8.0-2.0`

name: gatk-collect-oxog-metrics.4.1.8.0-1.0
body:
- Bump gatk version to 4.1.8.0
- Return None in json when oxoQ_score=nan

name: gatk-collect-oxog-metrics.4.1.4.1-1.6
body: * added a new input param for `dependencies`, this is useful when we want to make the process run after other process(es) from which the current process does not actually take any input. This is often referred as `mock dependencies`

name: gatk-split-intervals.4.1.4.1-1.0
body: * added NF version of the split-intervals tool

name: gatk-collect-oxog-metrics.4.1.4.1-1.4
body:
* allow specifying 'intervals' (in bed/bed-like file) for OxoG metrics collection
* added NF process for gathering multiple OxoG metrics and produce one OxoQ score

name: gatk-collect-oxog-metrics.4.1.4.1-1.3
body: * added tool info in extra_info JSON
